      options: ["It is the most expensive study design", "Randomization assigns participants to treatment or control groups by chance, minimizing selection bias and confounding variables, allowing the researcher to attribute differences in outcomes to the intervention rather than other factors", "It uses the most patients", "It takes the longest to complete"],
      correct: 1,
      rationale: "Randomization is the key feature that makes RCTs superior to observational studies. By randomly assigning participants, known and unknown confounding variables are distributed equally between groups, allowing causal inference about the intervention's effect."
