    pearls: ["-itis = inflammation (appendicitis, cholecystitis, meningitis); -ectomy = surgical removal (appendectomy, cholecystectomy); -ostomy = creating an opening (colostomy, tracheostomy)", "tachy- = fast, brady- = slow: tachycardia (fast heart), bradycardia (slow heart), tachypnea (fast breathing), bradypnea (slow breathing)", "hyper- = excessive, hypo- = deficient: hyperglycemia (high glucose), hypoglycemia (low glucose), hypertension, hypotension", "dys- = difficult/abnormal: dyspnea (difficult breathing), dysphagia (difficult swallowing), dysuria (difficult/painful urination)", "Joint Commission 'Do Not Use' abbreviations: never write U (write units), IU (write international units), QD (write daily), trailing zero (write 1 mg not 1.0 mg)", "The combining vowel 'o' is dropped when the suffix begins with a vowel: gastr + -itis = gastritis (not gastroitis)"],
