      rationale: "Per ACC/AHA guidelines, patients with functional capacity ≥4 METs (can climb stairs, walk uphill, do yard work) can proceed to surgery without further cardiac testing regardless of RCRI score. The ability to achieve 4 METs correlates with adequate cardiac reserve for the stress of surgery."
