    pearls: ["The 5 Rights of Medication Administration: Right Drug, Right Dose, Right Route, Right Time, Right Patient — foundational safety check", "NNT (Number Needed to Treat) = 1/ARR; lower NNT = more effective treatment; NNT of 1 = every patient benefits (ideal but rare)", "ALWAYS check the PDMP before prescribing controlled substances — required by law in most states", "Error-prone abbreviations: NEVER write U (units), QD (daily), QOD (every other day), trailing zero (5.0 mg), or missing leading zero (.5 mg)", "DEA Schedule II drugs (opioids, stimulants) cannot be refilled — a new prescription is required each time", "Deprescribing is as important as prescribing — medications should be discontinued when no longer indicated, benefits no longer outweigh risks, or patient goals of care change"],
